24. Simple Programs Using C++ STL**

Aim:

To demonstrate simple programs using *C++ Standard Template Library (STL)*.

Algorithm:

1. Include <vector> and <algorithm>.
2. Use STL containers and algorithms to perform operations.

Program:

#include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include <algorithm>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    vector<int> v = {5, 2, 9, 1, 7};

    sort(v.begin(), v.end());

    cout << "Sorted elements: ";
    for (int x : v)
        cout << x << " ";
    cout << endl;

    cout << "Max element: " << *max_element(v.begin(), v.end()) << endl;
    return 0;
}


Output:


Sorted elements: 1 2 5 7 9
Max element: 9


Result:

Successfully demonstrated *use of STL (vector and algorithm)* in C++.
